<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aaldiana D'Ozz on 03-16-2001 10:00 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">From well over a year ago now (and still posted on my guild website cause they still love to tease me about it  ;)):

I was with a group in Paw that included my guildmate Atrila (lvl 30 druid). We were doing ok on the xp and avoiding the trains pretty well until one found us. Our tank calls for evac and just as the LOADING, PLEASE WAIT shows up it occurs to me that for the first time in a long time, the evac I'm about to land from was from a druid and not my usual wizzie companion. 

My problem? I'm KOS with druids. (Call it a weakness but I just love hearing those halflings scream...something Atrila has teased me about in the past. Blame my DE connections. *grin*) 

Well, sure enough, as I appear in East Karanas I'm instantly attacked (figures this was one time those druids weren't camped). Needless to say, I died almost before I could see what was happening. So...I reappear at my bind spot by Paw, run to EK to get my body and then gate back to fight some more. 

Everyone is of course having a ball with this at my expense in guildchat. Not often a guildmember gets to kill their guild leader. 8) 

I tell the group that next time an evac is called I'm going to hit Divine Aura (since you can't evac with that spell on) and run for the zone instead. I figure its about the same odds and if I die, at least I'm not 3 zones away. 

Well, sure enough about an hour later we again have to evac. Just as I see the call for the evac I hit Divine Aura. 

It fizzles. 

I have never ever seen DA fizzle before in my entire EQ life. 

<FONT color=red>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...</font>

Damn druids. 


